        "title": "JFreeChart Get Legend Graphic",
        "body": "<p>In my application, I am showing data in a table as well as through a Dual Axis Bar/Line JFreeChart. To save some space (as the charts are being saved as PNG and put on PDF with iText PDF), I wanted to take the Graphics from the Legend, use them in the tabular view, and remove the legend. <\/p>\n\n<p>Is there a way to grab the icons that lie with the legend item? I have found the <code>LegendGraphic<\/code> class, which seemed like would be the method to retrieve the icon from the <code>LegendItem<\/code>, but have not found anything in the documentation for <code>LegendItem<\/code> that would indicate it does.<\/p>\n\n<p>It would be preferable if they were returned in an object that could easily be used to create a <code>com.itextpdf.text.Image<\/code>, such as <code>byte[]<\/code> or <code>java.awt.Image<\/code>.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 8302194,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "jfreechart"
        ],
        "score": 2,
        "accepted_answer_id": 8302953,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 2402
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [{
        "owner": {
            "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/632732029bf05854c17d0dea6c82dcb4?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
            "account_id": 81822,
            "user_type": "registered",
            "user_id": 230513,
            "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/230513/trashgod",
            "reputation": 206045,
            "display_name": "trashgod",
            "accept_rate": 100
        },
        "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
        "score": 3,
        "is_accepted": true,
        "last_activity_date": 1322530201,
        "creation_date": 1322517555,
        "body": "<p>You can get a series' <a href=\"http://www.jfree.org/jfreechart/api/javadoc/org/jfree/chart/LegendItem.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>LegendItem<\/code><\/a> using the chart renderer's <code>getLegendItem()<\/code> method. You can change a series' <code>Shape<\/code> using the methods of <a href=\"http://www.jfree.org/jcommon/api/org/jfree/util/ShapeUtilities.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>ShapeUtilities<\/code><\/a>, as shown in this <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/6665354/changing-the-shapes-of-points-in-scatter-plot/6669529#6669529\">example<\/a>. See also <a href=\"http://www.jfree.org/jfreechart/api/javadoc/org/jfree/chart/plot/DefaultDrawingSupplier.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>DefaultDrawingSupplier<\/code><\/a> for details of how <a href=\"http://www.jfree.org/jfreechart/api/javadoc/src-html/org/jfree/chart/plot/DefaultDrawingSupplier.html#line.279\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>createStandardSeriesShapes()<\/code><\/a> works.<\/p>\n\n<p>Addendum: Note that the renderer's <code>getLegendItem()<\/code> method works even if you create the chart with no legend or later use <code>chart.removeLegend()<\/code>. Once you have the <code>LegendItem<\/code>, you can use it's attributes as required.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>System.out.println(renderer.getLegendItem(0, 0).getShape());\nSystem.out.println(renderer.getLegendItem(0, 0).getFillPaint());\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
        "answer_id": 8302953,
